message.content: cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.SE. The paper discusses the development of a controlled natural language (CNL) for authoring competency questions (CQs) for ontologies. This falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as ontologies are used in knowledge representation and reasoning. The paper also mentions the use of natural language processing (NLP) techniques for processing CQs, which falls under the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Information retrieval (cs.IR) is also relevant as CQs are used to retrieve information from ontologies. The paper also discusses the evaluation of the CNL, which involves testing its coverage and accuracy, which falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and software engineering (cs.SE).
